Health Hazard Warning Issued Over Sobey's Own Beef Jerky
---------------------------------------------------------
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) is warning the public not to
consume Sobey's Own brand Beef Jerky products. It is possible that the
products contain the bacteria responsible for botulism in humans. Botulism
is a life-threatening illness caused by toxins produced by _Clostridium
botulinum_ bacteria. These products should not be consumed.
The products are sold in individually weighed packages containing
approximately 100 g product. All codes are affected. The Beef Jerky
products are:
Sobeys Own Beef Jerky, UPC code 206925 907671
Sobeys Own Spicy Beef Jerky, UPC code 201852 907510
These Beef Jerky products, manufactured by Sobeys Smokehouse, St. John's,
Newfoundland have been distributed only in the St. John's metropolitan
area. Sobeys Inc., Stellarton, Nova Scotia has voluntarily recalled the
products from the marketplace.
Foods contaminated with _C. botulinum_ bacteria may not look or smell
spoiled. Consumers should dispose of remaining product immediately or
return products to the point of purchase for a refund. There have been no
reported illnesses associated with the consumption of these products. The
Canadian Food Inspection Agency is monitoring the effectiveness of the recall.
